    <h2>üåê Web Tracking Technologies Demo</h2>

    <div class="tracking-info">
        <h3>1. HTTP Cookie (Client-Side Storage)</h3>
        <p>This is a demonstration of how a **First-Party Cookie** is set and read using JavaScript.</p>
        <p id="cookieStatus">Checking for a tracking cookie...</p>
        
        <script>
            // Set a cookie that expires in 1 day
            document.cookie = "user_id=abc123xyz; expires=" + new Date(Date.now() + 86400000).toUTCString() + "; path=/";

            // Check if the cookie was set
            const cookieValue = document.cookie.split('; ').find(row => row.startsWith('user_id='))?.split('=')[1];

            if (cookieValue) {
                document.getElementById('cookieStatus').innerHTML = '‚úÖ **Cookie Set/Read:** A tracking cookie with value **user_id=' + cookieValue + '** has been successfully set and read.';
            } else {
                document.getElementById('cookieStatus').innerHTML = '‚ùå **Cookie Not Found:** Could not set or read the tracking cookie.';
            }
        </script>
    </div>

    <div class="tracking-info">
        <h3>2. Simple Pixel Tracking (Image Beacon)</h3>
        <p>This invisible image (often 1x1 pixel) sends a request to a server, which can record information like the user's IP, time of visit, and page viewed.</p>
        <p>*(The browser loads this image without showing anything, sending data in the background.)*</p>
        
        <img src="https://example.com/track/pixel.gif?page=details" alt="Tracking Pixel" style="width:1px; height:1px; border:0; display:none;" aria-hidden="true">
        
    </div>

    <div class="tracking-info">
        <h3>3. Local Storage (Persistent Client-Side Data)</h3>
        <p>Local Storage is a more modern way to store larger amounts of persistent data in the browser, often used for user preferences or persistent identifiers.</p>
        <p id="localStorageStatus">Checking Local Storage...</p>

        <script>
            // Set a Local Storage item
            localStorage.setItem('session_token', 'token-jkl789');

            // Read the Local Storage item
            const token = localStorage.getItem('session_token');

            if (token) {
                document.getElementById('localStorageStatus').innerHTML = '‚úÖ **Local Storage Set/Read:** Stored value **session_token=' + token + '** in the browser\'s Local Storage.';
            } else {
                 document.getElementById('localStorageStatus').innerHTML = '‚ùå **Local Storage Not Found:** Could not set or read the Local Storage item.';
            }
        </script>
    </div>

